<br>
Fungus grove- shard dropping shiknars<br>
<br>
Ssra temple - pretty much everywhere<br>
<br>
Skyshrine - especially skyshrine.  Skyshrine is the untapped motherload of exp with lvl 55+ mobs , there are a bajillion mobs here level 55+ that are perfect for one group to kill.<br>
<br>
Griegs - MANY places here.<br>
<br>
Katta - the harder guards and guildleaders.<br>
<br>
Seru - Pretty much everywhere.<br>
<br>
Other Cities - especially paineel, neriak, and echo caverns evil class area.  Pretty much every city will do, though you may want to stick to evil cities for faction reasons.<br>
<br>
Sebilis - Mobs between ilis jail and trakanons lair.<br>
<br>
Chardok - almost the entire zone, especially down near royals.<br>
<br>
Kael - The entire zone, most obviously, the arena.<br>
<br>
PoG - The entire zone.<br>
<br>
PoM -  There are a few places, if you can get to them.<br>
<br>
HS - Deeper in.<br>
<br>
Skyfire -  Entire zone, esp. near VP entrance.<br>
<br>
The deep -  Entire zone<br>
<br>
VP - For those with really big balls and a death wish<br>
<br>
Acrylia - lower acrylia, if you can get key<br>
<br>
Tenebrous - vampyre tower<br>
<br>
Cazic Thule -  Entire zone<br>
<br>
<br>
Those are just some of the places where a single group can fight mobs that are level 55+ and will get extremely good exp.  There are other zones and many specific places in lower zones, that also have mobs with equal difficulty/level/exp.  Anyone who tries to claim that there aren't enough places to fight is full of it.  What they mean is that they're too lazy to go there, or more likely, too scared.  The idea of fighting mobs that can actually KILL you if your group messes up, seems lost upon many players in the upper levels nowadays.<br>
<br>
I remember fighting in the revamped paw when i was level 28, many mobs connned red to everyone in our group, and we wiped out several times, but it was great exp, it was a challange, and it was fun.  Hopefully the exp changes will encourage people to once again fight mobs that might actually kill them once and a while and will get people exploring areas they haven't been to before.  The reason people keep having exp group burnout, is because they keep fighting the same damn frogs in sebilis that have no chance of hurting them even after they've gotten 50+AA points.  Its time to move on people! STOP BULLYING THE WEAKEST MOBS YOU CAN FIND!<br>
